text:
Salah satu goals makam pahlawan yg ingin saya kunjungi. Tempatnya jauh dari pusat kota Rembang, karna memerlukan waktu tempuh selama ± 30 menit dari pusat kota. Agak kaget, karena sepi pengunjung. Padahal ekspektasi saya sangat ramai bahkan mungkin sesak. Ternyata sepi, hanya ada 1 bus rombongan dan beberapa sepeda motor.
Tempatnya luas, nyaman, dan asri banget. Sejuk juga karena lokasinya ada di dataran tinggi. Tempat parkir luas, nyaman, ada beberapa warung dan penjual jajanan.
textTranslated:
One of my goals is the hero's grave that I want to visit. The place is far from the city center of Rembang, because it takes ± 30 minutes to travel from the city center. A bit surprised, because there were no visitors. Even though my expectations were that it would be very busy, maybe even crowded. It turned out to be quiet, there was only 1 group bus and several motorbikes.
The place is spacious, comfortable and very beautiful. It's also cool because the location is in the highlands. The parking area is spacious, comfortable, there are several stalls and snack sellers.

name: byantara adi
text:
Salah satu situs sejarah yang merupakan makam dari salah satu pahlawan wanita Indonesia, RA Kartini, yang memperjuangkan gender equality dengan karya nya berupa kutipan surat2nya dengan sahabat pena nya bernama "Habis Gelap Terbitlah Terang".

Situs makam ini aslinya merupakan pemakaman keluarga Djojo Adhiningrat, dimana pada situs inj terdapat beberapa makam dengan nama akhir yang sama.

Selain makam RA Kartini terdapat makam dari Bupati Jepara yang merupakan suami beliau.
textTranslated:
One of the historical sites is the grave of one of Indonesia's female heroes, RA Kartini, who fought for gender equality with her work in the form of excerpts from her letters with her pen friend called "After Darkness Comes Light".

This grave site was originally the Djojo Adhiningrat family cemetery, where on this site there are several graves with the same last name.

Apart from RA Kartini's grave, there is the grave of the Regent of Jepara who was her husband.
title: Makam Raden Ayu Kartini

text: Waktu itu, mumpung lewat jadi sekalian mampir yaa. Pas kami masuk nggak ada tiket, hanya parkir saja. Walaupun ada tulisan tiket 1 orang 3rb. Alhamdulillah sudah 2 kali ke tempat ini. Tempatnya bersih sekali, parkir luas, kebetulan pas hari senin jadi sepi, hanya 1, 2 orang saja nggak banyak, dan untuk ziarah juga nggak buru², santai sampai puas juga foto²nya🤗 Sayangnya disana nggak ada yg jual bunga untuk kita ziarah, tp alhamdulillah tetep kita berdoa di pusara RA KARTINI, jadi kalau niatnya mau ziarah lebih baik bawa bunganya dr rumah atau sudah beli sebelumnya. Ada toilet bersih, mushola juga. Ada warung² juga tp mungkin bukanya cuma waktu weekend aja, kebetulan kemarin hanya 1 warung aja yg buka.
textTranslated: At that time, I was passing by so I might as well stop by. When we entered there were no tickets, just parking. Even though it says tickets for 1 person 3k. Thank God I've been to this place twice. The place is very clean, the parking area is spacious, coincidentally it's quiet on Mondays, only 1 or 2 people, not many people, and there's no rush for the pilgrimage, relax until you're satisfied with the photos🤗 Unfortunately there's no one there selling flowers for our pilgrimage, but thank God it's still there. We pray at RA KARTINI's grave, so if you intend to make a pilgrimage, it's better to bring flowers from home or buy them beforehand. There are clean toilets, prayer rooms too. There are also stalls but maybe they are only open on weekends, coincidentally only 1 stall was open yesterday.

address: Jl. Gatot Subroto No.8, Kutoharjo, Kec. Rembang, Kabupaten Rembang, Jawa Tengah 59219, Indonesia
name: Raden Oktova Gamma Star
text: This museum is located within the local government office complex of Rembang Regency, Central Java. I and my wife came here shortly before the outbreak of the Covid-19 pandemic. A large, peaceful, cool place with well preserved buildings and artefacts, including a room where RA Kartini gave lessons to girls, her bathroom and bedroom. There is also a library showing her writings and an inscription about her family tree.  Here I felt a direct connection between the real world where she spent her short married life until her death and what we read and hear about her. Our visit has left a deep impression in our hearts.  Clean toilets and musholla (moslem prayer place) outside of the museum but still within the government complex.
title: Museum R.A. Kartini Rembang

address: Jl. Gatot Subroto No.8, Kutoharjo, Kec. Rembang, Kabupaten Rembang, Jawa Tengah 59219, Indonesia
name: Rio Rinaldo
text: This museum has potential to be much more interesting and informative. During the eleven months Kartini lived here as the wife of Rembang regent, she had become the champion for the education of girls there as she did back in her hometown, Jepara. However this part of her life is not much explored and displayed save for some photos of her with her students. In the museum, which once was her residence, we could see her rooms, books and library, pictures, and many other belongings that once was hers. All without sufficient information. My favorite display is a black velvet kebaya that had become an iconic symbol of hers and a picture of her making batik.
title: Museum R.A. Kartini Rembang

address: Jl. Gatot Subroto No.8, Kutoharjo, Kec. Rembang, Kabupaten Rembang, Jawa Tengah 59219, Indonesia
name: puji maharani
text:
Went there at 7.20 AM because Google says it is open at 7.00 AM, turns out the opening hours is 8.00 AM-4.00 PM so the ticket desk was unattended. Thankfully, the staff were willing to open the museum earlier for me, and even provided an impromptu guide around the premises.

The museum itself is pretty insightful, as it opens the door to the past life of one of the most celebrated feminists in the history of Indonesia, and therefore has so much potential. The overall building maintenance and display of the exhibits could be improved, especially in the room that showcases Kartini's writings and books written about her.

If you are in Rembang, this museum is worth the visit. Plus, it will only cost you Rp2.000. Best to get yourself a guided tour for more stories on Kartini that you might not have heard yet.
title: Museum R.A. Kartini Rembang

name: Kusumo Wardoyo Cahyo Nugroho
text: Kali ini JAZMU mengunjungi Makam KH Soleh Darat di Semarang. KH Sholeh Darat, atau yang bernama lengkap Muhammad Sholeh bin Umar as-Samarani, adalah seorang ulama besar yang lahir di Jepara pada tahun 1820. Beliau dikenal sebagai salah satu ulama paling berpengaruh di Jawa pada masanya dan memiliki hubungan penting dengan dua pendiri organisasi Islam di Indonesia. Beliau adalah guru dan mentor bagi dua pendiri organisasi Islam terbesar di Indonesia, yaitu KH Hasyim Asy'ari (NU) dan KH Ahmad Dahlan (Muhammadiyah). Ajaran dan pemikirannya tentang Islam moderat, nasionalisme, dan pendidikan telah menginspirasi banyak orang dan terus relevan hingga saat ini.
textTranslated: This time JAZMU visited the grave of KH Soleh Darat in Semarang. KH Sholeh Darat, or whose full name is Muhammad Sholeh bin Umar as-Samarani, was a great cleric who was born in Jepara in 1820. He was known as one of the most influential clerics in Java at his time and had important relationships with the two founders of Islamic organizations in Indonesia. He was a teacher and mentor for the two founders of the largest Islamic organizations in Indonesia, namely KH Hasyim Asy'ari (NU) and KH Ahmad Dahlan (Muhammadiyah). His teachings and thoughts about moderate Islam, nationalism and education have inspired many people and continue to be relevant today.
title: Makam KH Sholeh Darat

Mbah Sholeh Darat.
His tomb complex is shaded by an open cupola. At the back end there is a brown wall that says "KH Soleh Darat's grave"
Inside this cupola are lined with graves from Mbah Sholet Darat's family. The pilgrims almost had difficulty finding a place to sit to pray.

name: VIRGA76
text:
KH Sholeh Darat, lahir di Desa Kedung Jumbleng, Kecamatan Mayong, Kabupaten Jepara pada tahun 1235 Hijriah bertepatan dengan tahun 1820 Masehi dengan nama lengkap Muhammad Sholeh bin Umar al-Samarani. Masa kecil hingga remaja KH Sholeh Darat dihabiskan dengan belajar Al-Qur'an serta ilmu agama dari ayahnya. Seperti ilmu nahwu, shorof, akidah, akhlak, hadits dan fiqih. Setelah lepas masa remaja KH Sholeh Darat menimba ilmu ke sejumlah ulama di Jawa maupun ulama di luar negeri.

Buku Sejarah dan Perjuangan Kiai Sholeh Darat diungkapkan, dalam mendalami ilmu keislamannya, dimulai dari belajar kitab-kitab fiqih kepada KH M Syahid di Pesantren Waturoyo, Margoyoso, Kajen, Pati. Di antaranya kitab Fathul Qarib, Fathul Mu’in, Minhajul Qawwim, Syarah al-Khatib dan Fathul Wahab. KH Sholeh Darat juga belajar Tafsir Jalalain karya Imam Suyuti pada Kiai Raden Haji Muhammad Sholeh bin Asnawi Kudus. Berikutnya belajar Nahwu dan Sorof pada Kiai Ishak Damaran Semarang dan belajar Ilmu Falak kepada Kiai Abdullah Muhammad bin Hadi Baquni yang juga salah seorang Mufti di Semarang.

Selanjutnya juga belajar Kitab Jauharut Tauhid karya Syekh Ibrahim al-Laqqoni serta Kitab minhajul Abidin karya imam Ghazali pada Sayid Ahmad Bafaqih Ba’alawi Semarang, belajar Kitab Masailul Sittin karya Abu Abbas Ahmad al-Mishri kepada Syekh Abdul Ghani Bima dan belajar ilmu tasawuf dan tafsir Al-Qur'an kepada Mbah Ahmad Alim.

Sedangkan di Makkah KH Sholeh Darat juga banyam menimba keilmuan agamannya pada para ulama seperti Syekh Muhammad al-Muqri al-Mishri al-Makki, Syekh Muhammad bin Sulaiman Hasballah dan Sayyid Ahmad bin Zaini Dahlan (Mufti Madzab Syafi’iyah).

Setelah beberapa tahun belajar, Kiai Sholeh menjadi salah satu pengajar di Makkah. Muridnya berasal dari seluruh penjuru dunia, termasuk dari Jawa dan Melayu. Beberapa tahun mengajar, Kiai Sholeh memutuskan kembali ke Semarang dan mengajarkan pengetahuannya kepada umat Islam di tempat tinggal asalnya. Kiai Sholeh pun mendirikan pusat kajian Islam berupa langgar atau mushala, yang kemudian berkembang menjadi pesantren kecil.

Tanggal 10 Syawal diperingati sebagai hari wafat gurunya pendiri Nahdlatul Ulama Yakni KH Soleh Darat. Pada tahun 2021 ini akan digelar haul pada Sabtu (22/5) di Bukit Bergota Kota Semarang, tempat Kiai Sholeh dimakamkan.
textTranslated:
KH Sholeh Darat, born in Kedung Jumbleng Village, Mayong District, Jepara Regency in 1235 Hijri coincides with 1820 AD with the full name Muhammad Sholeh bin Umar al-Samarani. KH Sholeh Darat's childhood to adolescence was spent studying the Qur'an and religious knowledge from his father. Such as nahwu science, shorof, belief, morality, hadith and fiqh. After his teenage years KH Sholeh Darat gained knowledge from a number of scholars in Java as well as scholars abroad.

Kiai Sholeh Darat's History and Struggle book revealed, in deepening his knowledge of Islam, starting from studying fiqh books to KH M Syahid at Pesantren Waturoyo, Margoyoso, Kajen, Pati. Among them are the books Fathul Qarib, Fathul Mu'in, Minhajul Qawwim, Syarah al-Khatib and Fathul Wahab. KH Sholeh Darat also studied Tafsir Jalalain by Imam Suyuti at Kiai Raden Haji Muhammad Sholeh bin Asnawi Kudus. Next he studied Nahwu and Sorof under Kiai Ishak Damaran Semarang and learned Astronomy from Kiai Abdullah Muhammad bin Hadi Baquni who is also one of the Muftis in Semarang.

Furthermore, he also studied the Kitab Jauharut Tauhid by Sheikh Ibrahim al-Laqqoni and the Kitab minhajul Abidin by imam Ghazali under Sayid Ahmad Bafaqih Ba'alawi Semarang, studied the Kitab Masailul Sittin by Abu Abbas Ahmad al-Mishri under Sheikh Abdul Ghani Bima and studied Sufism and Tafsir Al-Qur'an to Mbah Ahmad Alim.

While in Makkah KH Sholeh Darat also learned his religious knowledge from scholars such as Sheikh Muhammad al-Muqri al-Mishri al-Makki, Sheikh Muhammad bin Sulaiman Hasballah and Sayyid Ahmad bin Zaini Dahlan (Mufti of the Syafi'iyah Madzab).

After several years of study, Kiai Sholeh became one of the teachers in Makkah. His students come from all over the world, including from Java and Malay. After several years of teaching, Kiai Sholeh decided to return to Semarang and teach his knowledge to Muslims in his original residence. Kiai Sholeh also established an Islamic study center in the form of a langgar or mushala, which later developed into a small pesantren.

The 10th of Syawal is commemorated as the death day of the founder of Nahdlatul Ulama, KH Soleh Darat. In 2021 this will be called a haul on Saturday (22/5) at Bukit Bergota in Semarang City, where Kiai Sholeh was buried.

address: Jl. Bendungan, Randusari, Kec. Semarang Sel., Kota Semarang, Jawa Tengah 50244, Indonesia
name: Muhammad Farokhi
text:
Al-'Aalim Al-'Allaamah Asy-Syaikh Muhammad Sholih bin Umar as-Samarani al-Jawi asy-Syafi'i bahasa Arab: العالم العلامة الشيخ محمد صالح بن عمر السماراني الجاوي الشافعي‎ atau lebih dikenal dengan sebutan Mbah Sholeh Darat adalah merupakan seorang 'Ulama Besar di Semarang, Jawa Tengah.

Penambahan kata “Darat” pada akhir nama beliau disebabkan beliau tinggal di daerah yang bernama Darat, yaitu suatu daerah di pantai utara Semarang, tempat mendarat pelancong dari luar Jawa. Kini daerah Darat termasuk wilayah Semarang Barat. Penambahan ini adalah sesuatu yang lumrah sebagai ciri khas dari orang-orang yang terkenal di masyarakat. Seperti Mbah Kholil Bangkalan, Syeh Ihsan Jampes, Syeh Nawawi Banten, dan lain-lain.

Ayahnya Kiyai Umar merupakan salah seorang pejuang dan orang kepercayaan Pangeran Diponegoro di Jawa Bagian Utara, Semarang, di samping Kiyai Syada’ dan Kiyai Murtadha Semarang.

#Wikipedia
textTranslated:
Al-'Aalim Al-'Allaamah Ash-Shaykh Muhammad Sholih bin Umar as-Samarani al-Jawi ash-Shafi'i Arabic: العالم العلامة الشيخ محمد صالح بن عمر ماراني الجاوي الشافعي‎ or better known as Mbah Sholeh Darat is a a 'Great Ulama' in Semarang, Central Java.

The addition of the word "Darat" at the end of his name is because he lives in an area called Darat, which is an area on the north coast of Semarang, where travelers from outside Java land. Now the Darat area includes the West Semarang area. This addition is something that is commonplace as a characteristic of people who are famous in society. Such as Mbah Kholil Bangkalan, Syeh Ihsan Jampes, Syeh Nawawi Banten, and others.

His father, Kiyai Umar, was one of the fighters and confidants of Prince Diponegoro in Northern Java, Semarang, alongside Kiyai Syada' and Kiyai Murtadha Semarang.

HATI HATI syirik, luruskan niat dalam berziarah, jangan percaya ada keberkahan dengan meminta kpd ahli kubur melainkan mintalah kepada dzat yg maha perkasa Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

Sebab tidak ada amalan khusus yg pernah diajarkan Rasulullah shalallahu alaihi wa salam ketika berziarah, yg ada hanya doa/salam kepada ahli kubur. Bukan yasin atau tahlil atau amalan Bid'ah lain nya
textTranslated:
BEWARE of polytheism, straighten the intention in pilgrimage, do not believe that there is a blessing by asking the people of the grave, but ask the almighty essence of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

Because there is no specific practice that was ever taught by the Messenger of Allah, peace be upon him, when he was on a pilgrimage, there was only a prayer/greeting to the graves. Not yasin or tahlil or other Bid'ah practices

name: Elvita Yuli
text: Sebuah kebanggaan bisa mengulas museum RA Kartini, trinil, pahlawannya para wanita, keturunan Raja Majapahit. Melalui pemikiran2an Kartini yg cerdas, perempuan2 Indonesia di zaman itu akhirnya mendapatkan haknya yg layak sampai saat ini. Semoga Allah SWT berikan tempat yg layak bagi ibu kita Raden Ajeng Kartini. Aamiin..Yg lagi di Jepara, jgn lupa mampir ya ke museum ini. Biaya tiket masuknya murah kok. Seriously, this museum is worth to visit. Kita bisa menambah ilmu sejarah sekaligus menanamkan kecintaan pada para pahlawan di hati anak2 kita, sehingga anak2 penerus bangsa bisa menghargai apa2 yg sudah kita miliki s.d saat ini bukan malah jadi perusak negeri sendiri, naudzubillah. Dsini kita bisa tau seperti apa perjuangan Kartini, pemikiran2nya yg di tuangkan dlm bentuk tulisan tangan, bisa melihat meja jahit dan meja kerjanya, hobby, silsilah kerluarga, foto2 keluarga besarnya, foto makam, sampai foto tempat dikuburnya ari2 Kartini, dll. Di ruangan lain kita bisa lihat mata uang Indonesia dari thn 1945 s.d 2005, ad juga prasasti, kendi, jambangan dll. Komplitlah pokoknya.
textTranslated: It is an honor to be able to review the RA Kartini museum, the trinil, the female heroes, descendants of the Majapahit Kings. Through Kartini's intelligent thoughts, Indonesian women of that era finally got the rights they deserve to this day. May Allah SWT give a worthy place for our mother Raden Ajeng Kartini. Aamiin...Those who are in Jepara, don't forget to stop by this museum. The entrance ticket fee is cheap. Seriously, this museum is worth visiting. We can increase our knowledge of history and at the same time instill a love of heroes in the hearts of our children, so that the nation's future children can appreciate what we have up to now instead of becoming destroyers of our own country, naudzubillah. Here we can find out what Kartini's struggles were like, her thoughts expressed in handwritten form, we can see her sewing table and work table, hobbies, family tree, photos of her extended family, photos of her grave, even photos of where Kartini's graves are buried, etc. In another room we can see Indonesian currency from 1945 to 2005, as well as inscriptions, jugs, vases etc. Basically complete.
title: Museum RA Kartini

address: Jl. Kartini, Panggang I, Panggang, Kec. Jepara, Kabupaten Jepara, Jawa Tengah 59411, Indonesia
name: Reza Ali
text:
Tujuan wisata Edukasi, sangat cocok untuk anak anak.

Tidak sulit menemukan museum RA Kartini. Museum ini terletak di lun alun kote Jepara.

Parkir kendaraan cukup luas. Tiket masuk cukup terjangkau. Dewasa 8 ribu, anak anak 5 ribu.

Koleksi isi museum cukup lengkap. Ada beberapa foto yang dipajang berupa duplikasi atau repro.

Selain silsilah keluarga RA Kartini, koleksi disini  terpajang juga Fosil ikan. Fosil tersebut menjadi daya tarik sendiri bagi anak anak. Dan termasuk koin lama.

Untuk pelayanan staff cukup ramah dan informatif.  kondisi museum sangat terawar dan bersih
textTranslated:
Educational tourist destination, very suitable for children.

It's not difficult to find the RA Kartini museum. This museum is located in Jepara town square.

Vehicle parking is quite spacious. Entrance tickets are quite affordable. Adults 8 thousand, children 5 thousand.

The museum's collection is quite complete. There are several photos on display that are duplicates or reproductions.

Apart from RA Kartini's family tree, the collection here also displays fish fossils. These fossils are an attraction for children. And including old coins.

The staff service is quite friendly and informative.  The condition of the museum is very neat and clean
title: Museum RA Kartini

address: Jl. Gatot Subroto No.8, Kutoharjo, Kec. Rembang, Kabupaten Rembang, Jawa Tengah 59219, Indonesia
name: Ari Nugroho
text:
Perjalanan bagian hidup dari RA Kartini juga ada di Rembang. Peninggalannya masih tersimpan di  Museum RA Kartini. Jika Anda sedang melintas area Rembang kota, tak ada salahnya untuk mampir.

Lokasi museum RA Kartini tak jauh dari alun-alun Rembang. Suasananya nampak asri. Di depan pendapa terdapat taman dengan air mancur. Tiket masuknya juga cukup murah. Hanya Rp 2 ribu saja. Museum ini, dulunya merupakan tempat tinggal keluarga Kartini. Sehingga di dalamnya masih ada peninggalan berupa barang-barang rumah tangga. Ada meja makan hingga meja rias. Kata-kata mutiara dari RA Kartini juga menghiasi dinding-dinding Museum.

Dari buku panduan museum, disebutkan bahwa Museum RA Kartini didirikan pada 1967. Saat awal dibuka, museum ini hanya seluas kamar yang ditempati RA Kartini selama menjadi istri Bupati Rembang R.M.A.A Djojohadhiningrat. Dan, dalam perjalanannya museum pun berkembang. Luas bangunannya 3.732,4 meter persegi.

Koleksi museum ini berjumlah 224 buah yang terbagi menjadi enam jenis. Yakni ethografika 61 koleksi, histografika 110 koleksi, filografika 3 koleksi, Keramologika 25 koleksi, teknologinya 5 koleksi, dan seni rupa 20 koleksi.

Diantara benda-benda koleksinya ada bothekan. Yakni wadah berbentuk piramid lima susun berwarna coklat dan emas yang atasnya terdapat kuncup bunga. Fungsinya sebagai tempat jamu atau ramuan milik RA Kartini. Selan itu ada kotak jahitan, Bali, diorama RA Kartini dan RM Djojohadiningrat, diorama keluarga RA Kartini, dan kotak pataka.

Yang digunakan saat kirab malam 21 April. Dari Museum RA Kartini menuju makam beliau di Kecamatan Bulu. Jaraknya sekitar 20 kilometer dari Rembang Kota.Peninggalan-peninggalan barang pribadi RA Kartini juga ada di Museum ini. Ada baju adat Jawa, ranjang, cermin, meja rias, dan meja untuk merawat bayi.

Foto-foto keluarga RA Kartini selama masih hidup juga diabadikan di Museum ini. Seperti foto RA Kartini dan RM Djojohadiningrat saat menaiki kereta kuda. Pasangan ini sering melakukan kunjungan di wilayah Kadipaten Rembang saat itu.

Dan, yang tak kalah menarik, di museum juga ada tulisan RA Kartini. Ada buku Habis Gelap Terbitlah terang. Merupakan buku yang berisi surat RA Kartini dengan sahabatnya J.H Abendanon. Pembukuan pertama dilakukan J.H Abendanon dengan judul bahasa Belanda "Door Duisternis Tot Licht" dan terbit pertama pada 1911.

Buku ini tercatat pernah terbit beberapa kali. Kemudian cetakan kedua pada 1922 melalui penerbit Balai Pustaka dengan judul "Habis Gelap Terbitlah Terang: Boeah Pemikiran". Tahun 1938 buku kembali diterbitkan diterjemahkan oleh Armijn Pane. Tentunya masih banyak lagi koleksi-koleksi sejarah yang bisa dinikmati di Museum ini. Jadi, silahkan berkunjung, berwisata, sekaligus belajar sejarah.
textTranslated:
RA Kartini's life journey is also in Rembang. His relics are still stored in the RA Kartini Museum. If you are passing through the Rembang city area, there's no harm in stopping by.

The location of the RA Kartini museum is not far from Rembang square. The atmosphere looks beautiful. In front of the pendapa there is a garden with a fountain. The entrance ticket is also quite cheap. Only IDR 2 thousand. This museum was once the residence of the Kartini family. So inside there are still relics in the form of household items. There is a dining table and a dressing table. Aphorisms from RA Kartini also decorate the walls of the Museum.

From the museum guidebook, it is stated that the RA Kartini Museum was founded in 1967. When it first opened, this museum was only the size of the room occupied by RA Kartini while she was the wife of Rembang Regent R.M.A.A Djojohadhiningrat. And, along the way, the museum developed. The building area is 3,732.4 square meters.

This museum's collection totals 224 pieces which are divided into six types. Namely 61 collections of ethography, 110 collections of histography, 3 collections of philography, 25 collections of keramology, 5 collections of technology, and 20 collections of fine arts.

Among the objects in his collection is bothekan. Namely a brown and gold five-tiered pyramid-shaped container topped with flower buds. Its function is as a place for RA Kartini's herbal medicine or potions. Apart from that, there is a sewing box, Bali, a diorama of RA Kartini and RM Djojohadiningrat, a diorama of RA Kartini's family, and a banner box.

Which is used during the evening carnival on April 21. From the RA Kartini Museum to her grave in Bulu District. The distance is about 20 kilometers from Rembang City. RA Kartini's personal belongings are also in this museum. There are traditional Javanese clothes, a bed, a mirror, a dressing table and a table for caring for babies.

Photos of RA Kartini's family while she was still alive are also immortalized in this museum. Like the photo of RA Kartini and RM Djojohadiningrat while riding a horse-drawn carriage. This couple often visited the Duchy of Rembang at that time.

And, what is no less interesting, in the museum there is also an article about RA Kartini. There is a book After Darkness Comes Light. This is a book containing letters from RA Kartini and her friend J.H Abendanon. The first book was made by J.H Abendanon with the Dutch title "Door Duisternis Tot Licht" and was first published in 1911.

This book is recorded as having been published several times. Then the second printing was in 1922 through the publisher Balai Pustaka with the title "After Darkness Comes Light: Boeah Thought". In 1938 the book was published again, translated by Armijn Pane. Of course, there are many more historical collections that can be enjoyed at this museum. So, please visit, travel, and learn history at the same time.
title: Museum R.A. Kartini Rembang

text: Museum yg bagus,mengenal lebih sosok kartini dan keluarga juga tentang kota jepara. Lokasi dialun2 jepara, dengan fasilitas yg bagus. Kami datang dihari sabtu parkiran lengang dan gratis. Pengunjung museum juga hanya kami ber7. Tiket anak 5000 dan dewasa 8000. Dengan fasilitas bagus dan edukatif sayang memang jika museum ini sepi. Semua tertata rapi dan berurutan. Ada beberapa ruang pamer(4 ruang) dengan tema yg berbeda. Sekali-sekali perlu rasanya kita datang dan belajar sejarah langsung dg bukti2 sejarahnya,bukan cuma teori buku. Sepertinta destinasi wanib juga saat berkunjung di kota jepara,selain berwisata yg lain perlu juga berwisata sejarah.
textTranslated: A good museum, getting to know more about Kartini and her family as well as about the city of Jepara. Location in Jepara, with good facilities. We came on Saturday, the parking lot was empty and free. There were only 7 of us visiting the museum. Tickets for children are 5,000 and adults are 8,000. With good and educational facilities, it would be a shame if this museum was quiet. Everything is neatly arranged and in sequence. There are several exhibition rooms (4 rooms) with different themes. Every once in a while it feels like we need to come and learn history directly with historical evidence, not just book theory. It's like a popular destination when visiting the city of Jepara, apart from other tourist attractions, you also need to do historical tourism.

address: Jl. Kartini, Panggang I, Panggang, Kec. Jepara, Kabupaten Jepara, Jawa Tengah 59411, Indonesia
name: Maulana Bilal DP
text:
Museum terbaik di Jepara. Weekdays gratis, tapi weekend ditarik retribusi (sekitar Rp. 5000 untuk anak, dan Rp. 8000 untuk dewasa). Ada 3 ruangan, Ruangan 1 untuk R.A. Kartini dan Keluarga, Ruang 2 untuk Cagar Budaya di Jepara, dan Ruang 3 untuk Koleksi Kartini lain. Koleksi peninggalan R.A. Kartini dan keluarganya sangat lengkap, terutama di Ruangan 1&3. Ruang 2 menyimpan artefak dari jaman klasik sampai modern, termasuk dari jaman Hindu-Buddha. Yang unik, Prasasti Candi Angin di simpan di sini secara ex-situ. Sayangnya, sekitar 20-40% koleksi tidak diberi deskripsi, sehingga kalau pengunjung tidak paham konteks koleksi, maka akan kebingungan. Kebersihan terjaga, parkir tidak terlalu luas, dan ada kedai di samping barat museum. Overall, vibes museum memang dapet di sini.

Jangan lupa cek jagatkitasatu.worpress.com untuk konten ulasan wisata dan FnB lainnya!
textTranslated:
The best museum in Jepara. Weekdays are free, but weekends attract a fee (around Rp. 5000 for children, and Rp. 8000 for adults). There are 3 rooms, Room 1 for R.A. Kartini and Family, Room 2 for Cultural Heritage in Jepara, and Room 3 for other Kartini collections. The heritage collection of R.A. Kartini and her family are very complete, especially in Rooms 1 & 3. Room 2 stores artifacts from classical to modern times, including from the Hindu-Buddhist era. What is unique is that the Wind Temple Inscription is stored here ex-situ. Unfortunately, around 20-40% of the collection is not given a description, so if visitors do not understand the context of the collection, they will be confused. Cleanliness is maintained, parking is not too large, and there is a shop on the west side of the museum. Overall, you really get a museum vibe here.

Don't forget to check out jagatkitasatu.worpress.com for other travel and FnB review content!

text: Tiket masuk 5000. Museum Kartini yang berada di tengah kota Jepara dekat/ satu komplek dengan kantor kabupaten Jepara. Berisi foto bu Kartini, Sosrokartono, ayahanda, suami, dan putra serta keponakan dan keluarga besar. Terdapat replika fosil purba ikan hiu dan benda-benda peninggalan keluarga ibu Kartini dan akulturasi budaya yang ada di Jepara dengan Cina dan Arab melalui jalur perdagangan zaman dahulu.
textTranslated: Entrance ticket 5000. The Kartini Museum is located in the center of Jepara city, close to/in the same complex as the Jepara district office. Contains photos of Mrs. Kartini, Sosrokartono, father, husband and son as well as nephews and extended family. There are replicas of ancient shark fossils and objects left by Kartini's mother's family and cultural acculturation in Jepara with China and Arabia through ancient trade routes.

text: Jujur sih isi museum ini sangat terbantu dengan koleksi dari pameran di Erasmus Huis, kualitas foto dan keterangannya bagus. Di luar itu? Ya ala kadar aja sih menurut saya, mungkin karena memang Kartini rentang hidupnya enggak panjang, jadi yang dieksplorasi pun gak terlalu banyak selain foto dan cuplikan surat. Semoga nantinya bisa dibuat jadi lebih menarik lagi karena ini kan ikonnya Jepara ya, biar makin banyak wisatawan. Selain Kartini, museum ini juga memperlihatkan koleksi lain dari Candi dsb.
textTranslated: Honestly, the contents of this museum are really helped by the collection from the exhibition at Erasmus Huis, the quality of the photos and descriptions is good. Outside that? Yes, I think it's only moderate, perhaps because Kartini's life span wasn't long, so there wasn't much that was explored apart from photos and snippets of letters. Hopefully in the future it can be made even more attractive because this is Jepara's icon, so there will be more tourists. Apart from Kartini, this museum also displays other collections from temples, etc.

Mrs. Kartini's aura can touch the hearts and minds of visitors, especially those who like history.

Clean museum environment.
It is highly recommended to visit this museum.

address: Jl. Kartini, Panggang I, Panggang, Kec. Jepara, Kabupaten Jepara, Jawa Tengah 59411, Indonesia
name: Cindyy
text: Kedua kalinya ke museum Kartini setelah sekian lama, banyak perubahan dan sempet bingung masuknya gimana haha. Pas masuk disuruh isi buku kunjungan, terus udah. Aku nanya "Ngga bayar tiket mas?" Dijawab, "Mbaknya mau bayar tiket?" Hahah seketika malu. Jadi hari kerja emang ngga bayar tiket, tp weekend ada, lupa berapa. Rekomen ke sini, kemaren temenku ada yang museum date disini juga.
textTranslated: Second time going to the Kartini museum after a long time, lots of changes and I was confused about how to get in haha. When you entered you were told to fill out the visit book, and that was it. I asked "Didn't you pay for the ticket, bro?" He answered, "Do you want to pay for the ticket?" Haha, I'm embarrassed for a moment. So you don't have to pay for tickets on weekdays, but on weekends there are, I forget how many. Recommend coming here, yesterday my friend had a museum date here too.
title: Museum RA Kartini

address: Jl. Kartini, Panggang I, Panggang, Kec. Jepara, Kabupaten Jepara, Jawa Tengah 59411, Indonesia
name: Martha Zhahira El-Kutuby
text:
Museum RA Kartini terletak di Alun-alun Jepara Kota. Di depan Alun-alun pun ada Pendopo Bupati Jepara dan tempat pingit Kartini dahulunya.

Di dalam museum banyak sekali sejarah RA Kartini, saya sempat mengabadikan beberapa isi Surat RA Kartini kepada sahabatnya di Belanda yaitu Rosa Abendanon dan Stella.

Tiket masuknya 10rb per orang. Sudah mengeliling sekitar museum dan membaca sejarah RA Kartini dari lahir hingga meninggal.

Selamat menikmati.
textTranslated:
The RA Kartini Museum is located in Jepara City Square. In front of the square there is the Jepara Regent's Hall and where Kartini's residence used to be.

In the museum there is a lot of history about RA Kartini, I was able to capture some of the contents of RA Kartini's letters to her friends in the Netherlands, namely Rosa Abendanon and Stella.

The entrance ticket is 10 thousand per person. Have wandered around the museum and read the history of RA Kartini from birth to death.

Enjoy.
title: Museum RA Kartini

Cukup informatif bila ingin mengetahui R.A. Kartini. Banyak foto dan beberapa meja kursi yang digunajan oleh beliau. Hanya memang harus tekun membacai keterangan yang ada sebab tak ada pemandu.

Di akhir minggu, ada karcis yang harus dibayar. Senin-jumat gratis.

Ada ruang khusus juga yang membahas kakak Kartini, Kartono, yang merupakan pelajar dengan kemampuan medis dan menguasai 26 bahasa.
textTranslated:
Quite informative if you want to know R.A. Kartini. There are many photos and several tables and chairs used by him. You just have to be diligent in reading the information because there is no guide.

At the end of the week, there are tickets to be paid. Monday-Friday free.

There is also a special room that discusses Kartini's older brother, Kartono, who is a student with medical skills and masters 26 languages.
title: Museum RA Kartini

Disini kalian bisa dapet banyak pengetahuan baru yang seru dan menarik, terutama tentang Kartini dan Jepara
textTranslated:

Here you can get a lot of exciting and interesting new knowledge, especially about Kartini and Jepara

address: Jl. Kartini, Panggang I, Panggang, Kec. Jepara, Kabupaten Jepara, Jawa Tengah 59411, Indonesia
name: Diannisa Ar
text: Senin-jumat gratis. Display di ruangan yang menampilkan seluk beluk RA. Kartini menarik dan cukup jelas captionnya. Storyline jelas. Penerangan ok. Perlu menambahkan beberapa caption pada koleksi karena saya mengalami kesulitan untuk mengerti. Mungkin perlu melakukan riset mendalam tentang koleksi. Koleksi sangat menarik. Di ruangan selanjutnya ada kerangka hewan tapi tidak ada caption sehingga saya g tau jenis hewannya. Di ruang yang sama terdapat koleksi prasasti candi angin, keramik, dll. Cukup menarik. Ruang selanjutnya saya kurang begitu mengerti. Overall museum kartini bagus dan sangat bagus untuk edukasi. Staf museum sangat ramah.
textTranslated: Monday-Friday free. Display in the room showing the ins and outs of RA. Kartini's caption is interesting and quite clear. Storyline is clear. Lighting ok. Need to add some captions to the collection as I'm having difficulty understanding. It may be necessary to do in-depth research into the collection. Very interesting collection. In the next room there is an animal skeleton but there is no caption so I don't know what type of animal it is. In the same room there is a collection of wind temple inscriptions, ceramics, etc. Quite interesting. The next room I don't really understand. Overall the Kartini Museum is good and very good for education. The museum staff is very friendly.
title: Museum RA Kartini

address: Jl. Kartini, Panggang I, Panggang, Kec. Jepara, Kabupaten Jepara, Jawa Tengah 59411, Indonesia
name: Nadhifa Trihapsoro
text:
Museum yg bagus, menceritakan tentang sepak terjang dan peninggalan ibu Indonesia, RA Kartini. Masuk sini bayar 4500 untuk 2 org karena hari biasa

Museum tertata dengan rapih sehingga dapat membawa suasana ke zamannya. Terdapat dua ruangan, ruangan pertama menampilkan tentang seluk beluk RA Kartini mulai dari kehidypannya, surat-suratnya, serta org lain yg penting di kehidupannya, sedangkan ruangan kedua menanpilkan beberapa artefak dan kerajinan jepara.

Saya masih cukup bingung dengan ruangan kedua yg berisi beberapa artefak dan tengkotak paus, karena saya merasa kurang melihat korelasinya, selain itu di ruangan kedua ini kurang papan informasinya.
textTranslated:
A good museum, telling about the achievements and legacy of Indonesia's mother, RA Kartini. Come in here and pay 4500 for 2 people because it's a weekday

The museum is neatly arranged so that it can bring the atmosphere back to its era. There are two rooms, the first room displays the ins and outs of RA Kartini starting from her life, her letters, and other people who were important in her life, while the second room displays several Jepara artifacts and crafts.

I'm still quite confused about the second room which contains several artifacts and a whale box, because I feel like I don't see the correlation, besides that in this second room there is a lack of information boards.
title: Museum RA Kartini

text:
Museum yang terletak di jantung kota Jepara. Ada bbrp info yang bisa anda temui:
-Ada 3 serangkai yang terdiri dari RA Kartini dan 2 saudarinya.
-Bagaimana renda2 yg dibuatnya ,yg sangat terpengaruh oleh corak Eropa.
-Silsilahnya... .
-Bagaimana beliau meninggal.
Dan dipoligami dengan suami yang telah beristri 3 sebelumnya demi kepentingan politis.
- Bagaimana rupa Abendanon yang sering disebut sebagai teman curhat alias surat menyurat beliau.
-Barang2 peninggalannya.
-Betapa jeniusnya kakak RA Kartini yg menguasai 36 bahasa! Dll. Sangat rekomended utk menambah pengetahuan.
textTranslated:
Museum located in the heart of Jepara. There is some information that you can find:
-There are 3 series consisting of RA Kartini and her 2 sisters.
-How the lace she makes, which is very influenced by European patterns.
-The pedigree... .
-How he died.
And polygamous with a husband who has had 3 previous wives for political purposes.
- What does Abendanon look like, who is often referred to as his friend to confide in, aka his correspondence.
-Relics.
-What a genius, RA Kartini's sister, who can master 36 languages! Etc. Highly recommended to increase knowledge.
title: Museum RA Kartini

text: Ini kunjungan ke 2 ke kota rembang, namun baru kali ini mampir ke museum RA Kartini.. Bersih, teduh, agak spooky ya.. Heee.. Petugas ramah, dr jendela dapur terlihat rumah dinas bupati rembang yg sekarang.. Museum ini sendiri dl nya rumah bupati rembang yg tak lain adalah suami dr RA Kartini sendiri, di dalam nya terdapat foto keluarga dan perkakas yg pernah digunakan pd jaman beliau ada..di komplek itu jg ada rumah Kartini mengajar.. Tugas ke kota ini menambah wawasan sejarah di masa lalu.. Saran saja.. Untuk toilet agak dibuat nuansa lebih cerah biar gak merasa horor kalo mau numpang ke toilet.. Semoga kedepannya Museum ini dapat terus terjaga..
textTranslated: This is my second visit to the city of Rembang, but this is the first time I've stopped by the RA Kartini museum... Clean, shady, a bit spooky... Heee... The staff are friendly, from the kitchen window you can see the current Rembang Regent's official residence... The museum itself is in It's the house of the Regent of Rembang, who is none other than the husband of RA Kartini himself. Inside there are family photos and tools that were used during his time. In that complex there is also a house where Kartini taught. So... Just a suggestion... Make the toilets a bit brighter so you don't feel scared if you want to go to the toilet... Hopefully in the future this museum can continue to be maintained...
title: Museum R.A. Kartini Rembang

name: Abdul Ghofur
text: Kalau ke Rembang, wajib kesini sebagai bentuk penghormatan atas jasa-jasa ibu kita Kartini. Museum ini cukup luas. Ornamen jawa kuno benar-benar terasa. Ukiran kayu jati dan sejenisnya mendominasi isi bangunan ini. Dari segi manajemen, museum R.A. Kartini tampak mengalami kelesuhan dan disorientasi visi. Manajemen museum dimana-mana, di seluruh dunia, memang sulit. Harus ada terobosan baru dari seluruh stake holder di Kabupaten Rembang untuk menjadikan museum ini bukan hanya sebagai sarana edukasi kesejarahan, namun juga simbol kemajuan dan peradaban manusia Indonesia. Lebih khusus lagi adalah kemajuan daya pikir dan intelektualitas kaum perempuan Indonesia. Saya berharap benda-benda sejarah di museum ini dijaga dengan baik.
textTranslated: If you go to Rembang, you must come here as a form of respect for the services of our mother Kartini. This museum is quite spacious. You can really feel the ancient Javanese ornaments. Teak wood carvings and the like dominate the contents of this building. In terms of management, the R.A. Kartini appeared to be experiencing fatigue and vision disorientation. Museum management everywhere, throughout the world, is difficult. There must be a new breakthrough from all stakeholders in Rembang Regency to make this museum not only a means of historical education, but also a symbol of Indonesian human progress and civilization. More specifically, it is the advancement of the thinking and intellectual power of Indonesian women. I hope that the historical objects in this museum are well looked after.
title: Museum R.A. Kartini Rembang

text:
A witness historical Museum of R.A. Kartini, a smart javanese woman, one of the heroine who struggled women emancipation. She had tried hard to eliminate discrimination for women by educating them. You still find historical R.A. Kartini's school at that area
(Sebuah museum bersejarah yang menjadi saksi perjuangan RA Kartini, perempuan cerdas, seorang pahlawan wanita yang giat menghapus perbedaan  hak perempuan dengan cara mendidik mereka. Anda masih bisa menemukan sekolah R.A. Kartini di lokasi tersebut)
Selain digunakan sebagai tempat bersejarah juga digunakan sebagai pusat kesenian dan budaya di Rembang serta sebagai tempat layanan sosial dan kesehatan. Kebetulan kemarin saya menerima vaksinasi d tempat ini.
Trimakasih tim kesehatan, dan tim dari Polres Rembang yang sangat membantu masyarakat dalam kebutuhan menerima vaksin. Semoga kita semua diberi sehat walafiat selalu.
textTranslated:
A witness historical Museum of R.A. Kartini, a smart Javanese woman, one of the heroines who fought for women's emancipation. She had tried hard to eliminate discrimination for women by educating them. You still find historical R.A. Kartini's school at that area
(A historical museum that witnesses the struggle of RA Kartini, an intelligent woman, a heroine who was active in eliminating differences in women's rights by educating them. You can still find RA Kartini's school at that location)
Apart from being used as a historical place, it is also used as a center for arts and culture in Rembang as well as a place for social and health services. Coincidentally, yesterday I received a vaccination at this place.
Thank you to the health team and the team from the Rembang Police who really helped the community with their need to receive vaccines. May we all be given good health always.
title: Museum R.A. Kartini Rembang

Selain itu museum ini berisi perabotan-perabotan rumah tangga yang di pakai R.A. Kartini beserta suami.
textTranslated: R.A. Museum Kartini Rembang is located in Kutoharjo Village, Rembang District, Rembang Regency. This museum was previously the residence of RA Kartini and her husband Raden Adipati Djoyodiningrat. This museum contains the history of R.A. Kartini from childhood until she died. Many relics of his works are here. Apart from that, this museum contains household furniture that was used by R.A. Kartini and her husband.
title: Museum R.A. Kartini Rembang

address: Jl. Kartini, Panggang I, Panggang, Kec. Jepara, Kabupaten Jepara, Jawa Tengah 59411, Indonesia
name: Ayu Xavier
text: Harus kesiniiiiiii... Harus.. jangan lupakan sejarah. Sehari enggak cukup di museum Kartini. Museum nya lengkap. Semua tentang Kartini dan keluarga nya dan sahabat sahabat Belanda nya semua ada disini. Sekarang museum nya sudah nyaman. Kekinian. Memanjakan mata pengunjung. Bahagia deh. Duluuu museum Kartini kaku enggak kaya gini. Tapi sekarang sudah transformasi. Tiketnya murah meriah dan pake banget. Only 3rb. Pengunjung sudah dapet ilmu pengetahuan yang tak terhingga dan tak terlupakan. Yg pasti pengunjung dapat sejuta kebahagiaan. Di pintu masuk ada loket untuk membeli tiket. Serta tersedia oleh oleh khas Jepara. Oiya, kalo laper ada kantinnya juga loh. Dijual kopi khas Jepara. Harga nya 40rb. Harus cobaaa!! Tempat parkir nya ajiiib... Kekinian bgt. Sebelum masuk akan disapa oleh patung Kartini. Ada furniture dari Kartini dan keluarga nya, ada  foto fotonya juga. Ada tempat pengobatan juga. peralatan membatik. Lengkap kap kap  Diruang sebelah ada tulang ikan paus super big. Wow. Ada uang koin tempo dulu. Keramik dan Grabah. Ada peninggalan arca dari Candi juga. Yoni, lingga, Jaladwara, relief. Dan masih banyak lagi.
textTranslated: You have to come here... You have to... don't forget history. One day is not enough at the Kartini museum. The museum is complete. Everything about Kartini and her family and her Dutch friends are all here. Now the museum is comfortable. Contemporary. Spoil the eyes of visitors. I'm happy. In the past, the Kartini museum wasn't as stiff as this. But now it's a transformation. The tickets are cheap and very useful. Only 3k. Visitors have gained unlimited and unforgettable knowledge. What is certain is that visitors will get a million happiness. At the entrance there is a counter to buy tickets. As well as typical Jepara souvenirs available. Oh yes, if you're hungry there's a canteen too. Jepara specialty coffee for sale. The price is 40 thousand. Must try!! The parking lot is amazing... Very modern. Before entering you will be greeted by a statue of Kartini. There is furniture from Kartini and her family, there are photos too. There are treatment places too. batik equipment. Complete hood. In the next room there is a super big whale bone. Wow. There were old coins. Ceramics and Grabah. There are remains of statues from the temple too. Yoni, phallus, Jaladwara, relief. And many more.
title: Museum RA Kartini

address: Jl. Kartini, Panggang I, Panggang, Kec. Jepara, Kabupaten Jepara, Jawa Tengah 59411, Indonesia
name: jokocr
text:
Museumnya overall bagus, menarik. Sayangnya tidak ada pengawas disana jadi waktu sy kesana sy bingung parkir kendaraan, Krn g ada rambu/petugas yg mengarahkannya. Terlebih waktu sy berkunjung sy g tau pintu masuknya awalnya sampe sy tanya sm anggota TNI yg kebetulan lewat Krn kebetulan disitu dekat dgn korps TNI. Untuk penjelasan mengenai ibu Kartini ya menurut sy masih kurang, terlebih didalamnya dicampur dgn fosil dinosaurus dan juga patung² yg keterangan nya jg minim.
Mungkin dinas setempat bisa lebih menata kembali museumnya agar lebih jelas informasi tentang ibu Kartini, dan jikalau untuk fosil/benda2 sejarah lainnya jg bisa dijelaskan.
Sisanya sangat baik, semoga lebih bisa dikembangkan
textTranslated:
Overall the museum is good, interesting. Unfortunately there were no supervisors there so when I went there I was confused about parking the vehicle, because there were no signs/officers directing it. Moreover, when I visited I didn't know the entrance at first until I asked a TNI member who happened to be passing by because it happened to be close to the TNI corps. As for the explanation about Kartini's mother, in my opinion it is still lacking, especially since it is mixed with dinosaur fossils and also statues whose information is also minimal.
Maybe the local department can reorganize the museum so that the information about Kartini's mother is clearer, and fossils/other historical objects can also be explained.
The rest is very good, hopefully more can be developed
title: Museum RA Kartini

responseFromOwnerText: terimakasih atas lunjungannya kakak..ditunggu kedatangan berikutnya...
text:
Senin lalu mengunjungi Museum R. Ayu Kartini di Rembang dalam kunjungan tidak direncanakan. Saya datang jam 15.40 an masih diterima bahkan ada yang datang jam 16.30 masih diterima. Ibu Nana selaku pemandu baik sekali mengajak kami berkeliling museum dan berdiskusi mengenai sosok Kartini dan kehidupannya di Rembang dan Jepara.

Di museum ini, terjawab beberapa penasaran saya: dengan siapa ia berkirim pesan? Tenyata dengan isteri menteri pendidikan Hindia Belanda di Batavia yang pernah ia temui. Kenapa ia begitu cerdas untuk ukuran wanita pada zaman itu? Karena kakaknya bersekolah di Belanda dan ia mendapatkan buku-buku berbahasa Belanda seperti Max Havelaar dan bacaan mengenai Revolusi Perancis. Dan banyak lain.

Tiket masuk hanya 2.000 bisa menikmati rumah yang sama tempat Kartini tinggal bersama suami di Rembang, dengan peninggalan yang dirawat dengan baik, dan dibawakan oleh-oleh buku. Sungguh berkali-kali lipat yang pengunjung dapatkan.

Selamat berkunjung ke museum ini.
textTranslated:
Last Monday visited the R. Ayu Kartini Museum in Rembang on an unplanned visit. I came at 15.40 and I was still accepted, even some who came at 16.30 were still accepted. Mrs. Nana as the guide was very kind in taking us around the museum and discussing the figure of Kartini and her life in Rembang and Jepara.

At this museum, some of my questions were answered: who was he messaging with? In fact, he had met the wife of the Dutch East Indies education minister in Batavia. Why was she so intelligent for a woman of that era? Because his older brother studied in the Netherlands and he got books in Dutch such as Max Havelaar and reading about the French Revolution. And many others.

The entrance ticket is only 2,000 and you can enjoy the same house where Kartini lived with her husband in Rembang, with relics that are well cared for, and brought book souvenirs. What visitors get is really many times more.

Welcome to this museum.
title: Museum R.A. Kartini Rembang

address: Jl. Gatot Subroto No.8, Kutoharjo, Kec. Rembang, Kabupaten Rembang, Jawa Tengah 59219, Indonesia
name: Picca Picco
text:
Bangunan museum ini adalah rumah dinas suami RA Kartini saat menjadi Bupati Rembang. Bentuk rumahnya model Joglo Jawa (kurang terawat sih kalo menurutku). Di ruang belakang ada genting yang bocor & belum diperbaiki sehingga air hujan menggenang dan menyebabkan beberapa properti di ruang tsb lapuk. Suasana ruangannya juga lembab & kurang pencahayaan.

Benda-benda yang dipajang di museum ini, terbanyak adalah foto-foto repro RA Kartini & keluarganya, selanjutnya barang-barang rumah tangga yang pernah digunakan beliau (dan hampir semua kondisinya tidak terpelihara).

Ada juga sebuah ruang gelap yang di dalamnya terdapat penggalan isi surat-surat RA Kartini dari buku Habis Gelap Terbitlah Terang.

Saya menaruh harapan besar agar museum ini bisa dikelola dengan lebih baik & lebih terkonsep.
textTranslated:
This museum building was the official residence of RA Kartini's husband when he was Regent of Rembang. The shape of the house is a Javanese Joglo model (not well maintained, in my opinion). In the back room there are roof tiles that are leaking and have not been repaired, so rain water pools and causes some of the property in the room to rot. The atmosphere in the room is also damp & lacks lighting.

The objects on display in this museum are mostly reproduction photographs of RA Kartini & her family, followed by household items that she used (and almost all of them are not in good condition).

There is also a dark room in which there are fragments of RA Kartini's letters from the book Habis Gelap Terbitlah Terang.

I have high hopes that this museum can be managed better & more conceptually.
title: Museum R.A. Kartini Rembang

Yes, RA KARTINI was born in Jepara. Her fame is not only within Jepara, but is worldwide. For those who want to visit the museum today MONDAY-FRIDAY htm Free, for SATURDAY-SUNDAY between 5000-10000/person. The location is very strategic, namely in the corner of Jepara Square 1.

Salah satu destinasi obyek wisata di kabupaten rembang adalah museum RA kartini. Berada di komplek rumah dinas bupati rembang yang dekat dengan alun alun kota rembang.
Dimuseum ini kamu bisa menemukan barang barang peninggalan RA kartini yang merupakan salah satu pahlawan nasional emansipasi wanita, selain itu disini kamu juga bisa mengetahui riwayat RA kartini selama beliau masih hidup.
So tempat ini recomended buat kamu yang lagi singgah dan berkunjung ke rembang untuk datang ke museum ini.
textTranslated:
One of the tourist destinations in Rembang district is the RA Kartini museum. Located in the Rembang Regent's official residence complex which is close to the Rembang city square.
In this museum you can find items left by RA Kartini, who was one of the national heroes of women's emancipation. Apart from that, here you can also find out the history of RA Kartini while she was still alive.
So this place is recommended for those of you who are stopping by and visiting Rembang to come to this museum.
title: Museum R.A. Kartini Rembang

Untuk yang di Jepara lebih bercerita pada masa Kartini sebelum menikah,  sedangkan di Rembang bercerita tentang  masa Kartini setelah menikah dan menghabiskan sisa hidupnya.
Selamat berkunjung 😀
textTranslated:
The house, which is now used as the RA Kartini Rembang Museum, holds historical evidence in the form of relics of the residence and its contents. In Indonesia, there are two RA Kartini museums, namely in Jepara and in Rembang. In Jepara it tells more about Kartini's time before marriage, while in Rembang it tells about Kartini's time after marriage and spending the rest of her life.
Welcome to visit 😀

text: Museum Kamar Pengabdian R. A.  Kartini dahulu adalah rumah yang di diami R. A. Kartini setelah dipersunting oleh Raden Adipati Djoyodiningrat seorang bupati Rembang. Disini pengunjung dapat melihat,  kamar tidur R. A. Kartini,  alat penyimpanan obat tradisional,  karya sastra R. A.  Kartini dan beberapa peninggalan beliau yang lainnya.
textTranslated: The R. A. Kartini Devotion Room Museum was previously the house where R. A. Kartini lived after being married by Raden Adipati Djoyodiningrat, a regent of Rembang. Here visitors can see R. A. Kartini's bedroom, traditional medicine storage tools, R. A. Kartini's literary works and several other relics of his.

name: Roy Arnaldo Manurung /3bil2.
text: Biaya masuk hanya 3rb rupiah. Murah meriah. Menurut saya sejarah kartini di museum ini sudah lengkap. Foto-foto asli kartini berada di Belanda. Jadi yang dipajang di museum ini hanya kopian saja. Tidak ada guide. Jadi saya meminta penjaga museum untuk menjadi guide dadakan. Yang saya dapatkan tentang sejarah Kartini di museum ini ternyata lebih dari yang saya pelajari selama sekolah dahulu dan membuat saya terkaget-kaget. Selain bangunan khusus sejarah Kartini, ada bangunan lain yg berisi benda-benda purbakala yang ditemukan di Jepara. Ada fosil ikan purbakala yang sangat besar dengan panjang 15 meter (foto terlampir)
textTranslated: The entrance fee is only 3 thousand rupiah. Cheap. In my opinion, the history of Kartini in this museum is complete. The original photos of Kartini are in the Netherlands. So what is displayed in this museum is only a copy. There are no guides. So I asked the museum guard to be an impromptu guide. What I learned about Kartini's history at this museum turned out to be more than what I learned during school and surprised me. Apart from buildings specifically for Kartini's history, there are other buildings containing ancient objects found in Jepara. There is a very large ancient fish fossil with a length of 15 meters (photo attached)
title: Museum RA Kartini

Terus petunjuk untuk pintu masuknya jg kurang jelas sih, tau pintu masuk jg hasil tanya sm korps TNI yg kebetulan lewat, petunjuk pintu masuknya minim. Itu kesan pertama sy, masuk kesini kebetulan weekdays jadi masih gratis weekend bayar 5.000,- kondisi didalam nya itu bersih, tempatnya jg bagus sih, peninggalan barang2nya jg masih terawat. Sayangnya buat penjelasan tentang RA. Kartini nya masih minim sih, disini menurut sy museumnya dicampur2 Krn didalam ada fosil dinosaurus juga, dan ada peninggalan2 seperti guci dll.
Tempatnya g terlalu luas, mungkin kalo ditata sedemikian rupa bakal lebih menarik pengunjung lagi.
textTranslated:
This is my first time here, the first impression of coming here was that I was confused about finding a parking lot. Because there are no instructions for parking motorbikes here, if the car is in front of it. Then the instructions for the entrance are also not clear, I also found out about the entrance as a result of asking a TNI corps officer who happened to be passing by, the instructions for the entrance were minimal. That was my first impression, coming here happened to be on weekdays so it was still free on weekends and paid 5,000,- the conditions inside were clean, the place was also nice, the remains of the items were still well maintained. Unfortunately for an explanation about RA. Kartini is still minimal, here in my opinion the museum is mixed because inside there are dinosaur fossils too, and there are relics such as jars, etc.
The place is not too big, maybe if it was arranged in such a way it would attract more visitors.

Kebanyakan foto2, lukisan dan tulisan2 aja.  Masukkan aja sih,  Kalau bisa di tambahkan diorama 3D atau film ttg kartini atau apa gitu yg bisa menarik untuk anak2,
textTranslated: The maintenance is a bit lacking, at the entrance there is a large Kartini statue which the children really enjoyed looking at (understandably RA Kartini is popular among school children) but inside it turns out the collection is small. Mostly photos, paintings and writings.  Just put it in. If possible, add a 3D diorama or a film about Kartini or something like that that can be interesting for children.

text:
Lokasi di tengah kota,
Koleksi lumayan menarik...penataan mungkin bisa ditata lebih bercerita...misal seperti barang-barang dari masa kecil sampai dewasa....
Koleksi tidak begitu banyak.

Sedikit masukan mungkin penataan dan kuratorial bisa diubah supaya terlalu banyak tempelan cerita/foto/ tulisan supaya pengunjung bisa lebih fokus pada objek museum.
Yg menarik buat saya yaitu beberapa furniture Antique - yang dikonservasi.
textTranslated:
Location in the city center,
The collection is quite interesting... the arrangement could perhaps be arranged to tell more of a story... for example, items from childhood to adulthood...
Collection not so much.

With a little input, perhaps the arrangement and curatorial could be changed so that there are too many story/photo/writing posts so that visitors can focus more on the museum objects.
What's interesting for me is some of the antique furniture - which has been conserved.
title: Museum RA Kartini

address: Jl. Kartini, Panggang I, Panggang, Kec. Jepara, Kabupaten Jepara, Jawa Tengah 59411, Indonesia
name: Retno Dwi Cahyani
text: Cocok bagi teman-teman pecinta sejarah dan ingin menyelami masa lampau lebih dalam. Semua peninggalan sejarah dari Ibu Kartini masih terpajang dengan baik serta tidak lupa terdapat penjelasan-penjelasan dibawahnya. Jadi pengunjung juga cukup mengerti walau tidak dijelaskan secara rinci. Tempatnya sebenarnya bersih cuma ada beberapa sudut yang tidak begitu terawat, mungkin karena musium ini tempat bersejarah dan banyak orang yang belum terlalu berminat belajar disini. Melihat peninggalan-peninggalan yang cukup banyak dan masih terawat tempat ini masih asik untuk kita telusuri dan menikmati belajar dari kehidupan ibu kita Kartini😊
textTranslated: Suitable for friends who love history and want to dive deeper into the past. All the historical relics of Mrs. Kartini are still well displayed and don't forget to include explanations below. So visitors also quite understand even though it is not explained in detail. The place is actually clean, there are only a few corners that are not well maintained, maybe because this museum is a historical place and many people are not too interested in studying here. Seeing the many relics that are still well maintained, this place is still fun for us to explore and enjoy learning from the life of our mother Kartini😊
title: Museum RA Kartini

address: Jl. Kartini, Panggang I, Panggang, Kec. Jepara, Kabupaten Jepara, Jawa Tengah 59411, Indonesia
name: Hamid Anwar
text: Selain menampilkan aneka foto lawas keluarga RA Kartini, tempat ini juga menyimpan sejarah Jepara mulai dari masa Hindu Buddha, hingga masa Portugis. Senin sampai jumat masuk gratis tetapi toilet membayar 2000. Ada juga kerangka ikan raksasa yang dipajang pada ruangan yang menampilkan aneka temuan artefak arkeologi.
textTranslated: Apart from displaying various old photos of RA Kartini's family, this place also holds the history of Jepara from the Hindu Buddhist era to the Portuguese era. Monday to Friday entry is free but the toilet costs 2000. There is also a giant fish skeleton on display in the room which displays various archaeological artifact finds.
title: Museum RA Kartini

Ada lukisan foto juga.

Di museum juga dijual barang kerajinan jepara seperti kerajinan monel dan tenun teroso.

RA Kartini history tour. It's best before going to this museum to watch the film starring Christine Hakim, Dian Sastro, Acha Septriasa, et al so you can imagine the biographical picture.

There are several original wooden carved items such as tiger brackets, tables and chairs which are the legacy of RA Kartini.

There are photo paintings too.

The museum also sells Jepara handicrafts such as monel crafts and teroso weaving.

name: Sambudi Parto
text:
Museum ini didirikan saat pemerintahan Bupati Soemarno Djojomardowo pada tanggal 30 Maret 1975, dan peresmiannya dilakukan pada 21 April 1977 oleh Bupati Soedikto.
Peninggalan purba di museum ini adalah kerangka ikan besar dari perairan Karimunjawa. Ikan tersebut sering disebut dengan nama Ikan Jokotuo. Kerangka ikan yang mirip bisa dilihat jika berkunjung di bukit Jokotuo, Karimunjawa.
Mungkin megalodon pernah hidup di perairan Jepara
textTranslated:
This museum was founded during the reign of Regent Soemarno Djojomardowo on March 30 1975, and its inauguration was carried out on April 21 1977 by Regent Soedikto.
The ancient relic in this museum is a large fish skeleton from the waters of Karimunjawa. This fish is often called the Jokotuo Fish. A similar fish skeleton can be seen if you visit Jokotuo Hill, Karimunjawa.
Maybe megalodon once lived in Jepara waters
title: Museum RA Kartini

Museum ini didirikan pada 30 Maret 1975 pada masa pemerintahan BupatiSoemarno Djojomardowosementara peresmiannya dilakukan pada 21 April 1977 oleh BupatiSoedikto.Museum ini terdiri dari 3 buah gedung yang dibangun di atas area seluas 5.210 m2yangapabila dilihat dari atas gedung - gedung tersebut berbentuk huruf K,T, dan N yang merupakan singkatan dari KARTINI.Fasilitasfasilitas yang tersedia di Museum Kartini:*.Cafetaria*.Ruang Panggung Seni Teatrikal (Opera)*.Ruang Bioskop Film Kartini*.Toko Sovenir*.Toilet*.Taman Parkir
textTranslated: Kartini Museum is a museum located in Jepara district, Central Java Province. This museum was founded on March 30, 1975 during the reign of Regent Soemarno Djojomardowo, while its inauguration was carried out on April 21, 1977 by Regent Soedikto. This museum consists of 3 buildings built on an area of ​​5,210 m2 which, when viewed from above, are shaped like the letters K, T, and N is an abbreviation for KARTINI. Facilities available at the Kartini Museum: *. Cafeteria *. Theatrical Arts Stage Room (Opera)
title: Museum RA Kartini
